    • recreateThrowable

      public static Throwable recreateThrowable(String type, String message, List<String> backtrace) throws ParseException, ClassNotFoundException, NoSuchConstructorException, AmbiguousConstructorException, ReflectiveOperationException
      Recreate an exception from a type name, a message and a backtrace (created from JesqueUtils.createBacktrace(Throwable)).

      Limitations:
      This method cannot recreate Throwables with unusual/custom Constructors.

      • If the message is non-null and the cause is null, there must be a Constructor with a single String as it's only parameter.
      • If the message is non-null and the cause is non-null, there must be a Constructor with a single String as it's only parameter or a Constructor with a String and a Throwable as its parameters.
      • If the message is null and the cause is null, there must be either a no-arg Constructor or a Constructor with a single String as it's only parameter.
      • If the message is null and the cause is non-null, there must be either a no-arg Constructor, a Constructor with a single String as its only parameter or a Constructor with a String and a Throwable as its parameters.
      Parameters:
      type - the String name of the Throwable type
      message - the message of the exception
      backtrace - the backtrace of the exception
      Returns:
      a new Throwable of the given type with the given message and given backtrace/causes
      Throws:
      ParseException - if there is a problem parsing the given backtrace
      ClassNotFoundException - if the given type is not available
      NoSuchConstructorException - if there is not a common constructor available for the given type
      AmbiguousConstructorException - if there is more than one constructor that is viable
      InstantiationException - if there is a problem instantiating the given type
      IllegalAccessException - if the common constructor is not visible
      InvocationTargetException - if the constructor threw an exception
      ReflectiveOperationException
      See Also:
      • createBacktrace(Throwable)
